<section id="fs-idm489541632" class="section-summary">
<list id="fs-idm360485696" list-type="enumerated" start-value="6">
<item>How can managers reap benefits from diversity and mitigate its challenges?</item>
</list>
<para id="fs-idm357896896">By approaching diversity and diversity issues in a thoughtful, purposeful way, managers can mitigate the challenges posed by a diverse workforce and enhance the benefits a diverse workforce can offer.</para>
<para id="fs-idm509548640">Managers can work to make sure that the efforts and initiatives they enact to increase diversity in the workplace come from a perspective that ensures and strives for equity and fairness, not simply one that will benefit the company’s bottom line.</para>
<para id="fs-idm358941296">Using an integration-and-learning perspective strongly links diversity to the work and success of the firm by viewing cultural identity, different life experiences, skills, and perspectives from members of diverse cultural identity groups as a valuable resource.</para>
</section>
