<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm370175728"><term>integration-and-learning perspective</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm353040096">Posits that the different life experiences, skills, and perspectives that members of diverse cultural identity groups possess can be a valuable resource in the context of work groups.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm361757440"><term>access-and-legitimacy perspective</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm365392928">Focuses on the benefits that a diverse workforce can bring to a business that wishes to operate within a diverse set of markets or with culturally diverse clients.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm383622816"><term>discrimination-and-fairness perspective</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm383084048">A culturally diverse workforce is a moral duty that must be maintained in order to create a just and fair society.</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
